headline: Lennar & KB Home Face Tougher Housing Market, Goldman Sachs Cuts Forecast Amid Slowing Demand
summary: Goldman Sachs analyst Susan Maklari reiterated a Neutral rating on the shares of Lennar Corp (NYSE:LEN) and lowered the price forecast to $141.00 from $150.00. The analyst reiterated a Neutral rating on the shares of KB Home (NYSE:KBH) and reduced the price forecast to $72.00 from $81.00. The analyst lowered the first-quarter estimates for LEN and KBH due to a tougher operating environment, with weaker demand leading to higher incentives and reduced profitability.
